        <p>We are proud to offer special accessible performances for patrons with hearing or vision loss during the 2013 Free Shakespeare in the Park Season. For general information about Shakespeare in the Park, please contact <a href="mailto:info@publictheater.org" class="lowercase">info@publictheater.org</a>.</p><br />
        <p><b>ACCESSIBLE PERFORMANCES FOR <i>THE COMEDY OF ERRORS</i><br />Audio Described Performance:</b> June 8<br />A service for theatergoers with moderate to severe vision loss, sponsored by Theatre Development Fund (TDF). For more information or for tickets in the Audio Described section, please contact Sarah Aziz, TDF Accessibility Program Manager at 212.912.9770 ext. 382 or <a href="mailto:saraha@tdf.org" class="lowercase">saraha@tdf.org</a></p>
        <p><b>Sign Language Interpreted Performance:</b> June 21<br />For more information, please visit <a href="HandsOn.org" target="_blank" class="lowercase">HandsOn.org</a></p>
        <p><b>Open Caption Performance:</b>June 22<br />A service for patrons with slight to profound hearing loss with screens visible from any seat in the theater. Provided, in part, by Theatre Development Fund’s TAP Plus Program in partnership with the New York State Council on the Arts. For more information or for tickets, please contact Sarah Aziz, TDF Accessibility Program Manager at 212.912.9770 ext. 382 or <a href="mailto:saraha@tdf.org" class="lowercase">saraha@tdf.org</a></p>
        <p><b>ACCESSIBLE PERFORMANCES FOR <i>LOVE'S LABOUR'S LOST, A NEW MUSICAL</i><br />Audio Described Performance:</b>August 3<br />​A service for theatergoers with moderate to severe vision loss, sponsored by Theatre Development Fund (TDF). For more information or for tickets in the Audio Described section, please contact Sarah Aziz, TDF Accessibility Program Manager at 212.912.9770 ext. 382 or <a href="mailto:saraha@tdf.org" class="lowercase">saraha@tdf.org</a></p>
        <p><b>Sign Language Interpreted Performance:</b> August 4<br />For more information, please visit <a href="HandsOn.org" target="_blank" class="lowercase">HandsOn.org</a>.</p>
        <p><b>Open Caption Performance:</b> August 17<br />A service for patrons with slight to profound hearing loss with screens visible from any seat in the theater. Provided, in part, by Theatre Development Fund’s TAP Plus Program in partnership with the New York State Council on the Arts. For more information or for tickets, please contact Sarah Aziz, TDF Accessibility Program Manager at 212.912.9770 ext. 382 or <a href="mailto:saraha@tdf.org" class="lowercase">saraha@tdf.org</a></p><br />
